'''Ainulindalë''' or '''Music of the Ainur''' can refer to:
==Middle-earth==
* The First [[Music of the Ainur]], which created the world, narrated by [[Rúmil]] in his [[Ainulindalë (Rúmil's work)|''Ainulindalë'']].
* The [[Second Music of the Ainur]], which will re-create the world.

==Chapters==
*'''''[[Ainulindalë]]''''', the first part of ''[[The Silmarillion]]''.
* ''[[The Music of the Ainur]]'', the second chapter of ''[[The Book of Lost Tales Part One]]''.
*''[[Ainulindalë (Lost Road)]]'', the seventh chapter of ''[[The Lost Road and Other Writings]]''.
*''[[Ainulindalë (Morgoth's Ring)]]'', the first chapter of ''[[Morgoth's Ring]]''.
==Popular Media==
* [[Ainulindale (band)]], a French folk metal band.
** ''Ainulindale'', a song by the French band in their album ''[[The Lay Of Leithian (album)|The Lay Of Leithian]]''.
* [[Ainulindale Ensemble]], an Italian orchestral jazz group.
